== 1. 🎯 Why We Exist: Strategy & Mission ==
Our strategy centers on solving the "binary fact-check" problem through transparent, multi-perspective automation.

* 🔗 **[[Strategy & Mission>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Strategy.WebHome]]**: Mission, automation philosophy, and market positioning.

== 2. 🤝 How We Work: Culture & Collaboration ==
We combine human-centric values with high-velocity, consent-based processes.

* 🔗 **[[Culture & Collaboration>>FactHarbor.Organisation.How-We-Work-Together.WebHome]]**: Workplace values, decision-making (Sociocracy 3.0), and contributor guides.

== 3. ⚖️ How We Are Structured: Governance ==
Our governance ensures neutrality and "system-over-data" integrity.

* 🔗 **[[Governance>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Governance.WebHome]]**: Governance structure, roles, and the "Fix the System" principle.

== 4. 📜 Our Rules: Legal & Compliance ==
The formal framework protecting our mission and our users.

* 🔗 **[[Legal & Compliance>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.WebHome]]**: Statutes, open-source licenses, and public policies (Privacy/Transparency).

----

== 🗺️ Visual References ==
* **[[Diagrams>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Diagrams.WebHome]]**: Governance structures and operational domain maps.

== 💡 Key Principles ==
* **AI-First**: AKEL evaluates content; humans refine the system.
* **Radical Transparency**: Every decision and metric is public.
* **Consent-Based**: We move fast by seeking "no principled objections."
* **Swiss Neutrality**: Protected by our non-profit association status.

